parameters:
...Are you also a banished criminal? Or perhaps a daughter
of this island? I used to run a band of thieves near Edo,
but I was captured after being decimated by a single girl.
Ever heard of Mouse Komachi? She was really strong...

...Oh, is that so? (It seems my true identity hasn't been
discovered... That's a relief.)

This house smells nice... There's even a vase, I wonder if
the previous resident was a woman?
Karin here. Thank you for shielding me the other day.

No need to mention it. I was surprised you stood up to that
violent exile leader and his henchmen. And I heard you even
beat down two more of them afterward?
Eh...! How do you know about that?

Well, it's such a small island. Rumors spread quickly, you
know? Hehe...
Um... Your name is Kachou-san, right?

Yes. I am Kachou, who was exiled from Edo. I've been living
on this desolate island for two years now.

This island can't produce rice, so there's very little food.
That's why people starve to death every year... And we have
to give up the fish we catch to the exile leader...

...Just between us, Karin-san, do you have any plans to
escape from this island?
--Eh!? No, I haven't thought of anything like that--!

Because when you were talking to the exile leader, you said
'I'll be in your care for a while'...

Hehe, don't worry. I won't tell anyone. It's something
everyone who's been exiled to this island thinks about at
least once. I thought the same when I first arrived.

But... there's no way to escape since there isn't a single
boat on this island. The ship that comes once a month leaves
immediately after it arrives, and even if we were to seize
it, we don't have the sailing skills like a ship's
captain...

That's true... The sea was quite rough on the way here... I
definitely couldn't handle a boat myself...

Unfortunately, no one has ever escaped from this island
before. So it's better not to hold onto hope for getting off
the island too much. As a senior resident of this island,
that's an important piece of advice I can give you, Karin-
san.

You must be hungry. If you have a fishing rod, you can catch
fish, so it would be good to ask Kisanosuke-san for help.

He lives in the hut to the right of mine. He used to be a
fisherman, so he's skilled at catching fish. He also makes
his own fishing gear.

Thank you, Kachou-san! I'll go ask Kisanosuke-san next door
if he can make me a fishing rod!

If you get a fishing rod from Kisanosuke-san, you can fish
at [Southern Beach]. I think someone with good reflexes like
Karin-san will be able to catch a lot.
